## 🎨 TailwindCSS

- Use Tailwind utility classes only — no inline `style={{}}` unless absolutely necessary (e.g. dynamic values not possible with utilities)
- Use CSS variables for design tokens in `globals.css`, reference via Tailwind config
- Prefer `cn()` utility (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Do not use `@apply` in component files — only in `globals.css` for base styles
- Responsive: always mobile-first (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`)
- Dark mode: use `dark:` prefix consistently — don't mix manual class toggling with Tailwind dark mode

```typescript
// ✅ Correct
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'
<div className={cn('base-class', isActive && 'active-class', className)} />
```

